AmaZulu King MisuZulu KaZwelithini. DURBAN - A court application to stop AmaZulu King Misuzulu from addressing the Battle of Isandlwana commemoration has been dismissed with costs. The High Court in Pietermaritzburg said the applicant does not have the right to file an application and ruled that the application is not urgent. READ: Legal battle over Zulu King's commemoration speech A faction of the Zulu Royal Family wanted the courts to block the AmaZulu King's speech. It comes as a succession battle for the monarchy rages on. READ: Legal battles may tarnish image of AmaZulu nation: cultural expert Some family members say the King can't address the commemoration as his kingship is not yet confirmed. This year marks 143 years since AmaZulu warriors defeated the British army in the hills of Isandlwana in Nquthu, northern KwaZulu-Natal.